\f0\b0  ordinance that was proposed a year ago is expected to come before the county's Board of Commissioners May 11. It would amend the county zoning ordinance to allow small wind and solar projects outside the Rural Preservation District, where they are now prohibited.\
Meanwhile, John and Mary Smith can't get permits for a small turbine they were hired to install south of 
\f1\b Meridian
\f0\b0  in an area outside the Rural Preservation District. The turbine is now lying on the site while the Smiths seek a permit. While the county is considering a 
